@tqchen Thanks for clarifying that, I'm working on getting that ported to C++ at the moment - a quick question about conventions:
Specifying a schedule requires touching functions like Stage::split. This function is not prefixed with the EXPORT macro, but is added to the global registry as "_StageSplitByFactor". What would be the preferred way of accessing this and similar functions? Should I add the EXPORT macro and use it directly, or go via the registry?

This affects other functions too such as ScheduleNode::make (depended on by create_schedule), and Schedule::operator[]. At the moment for testing purposes I'm just adding EXPORT to all of these, but I'm wondering what would be the preferred way?

Your commit resolves the problem, everything is working great now! Thanks. For reference, here's what the custom tensor for pytorch ended up looking like.

```
@tvm.register_extension
class FireTensor(object):
    _tvm_tcode = tvm.TypeCode.ARRAY_HANDLE

    def __init__(self, tensor):
        self.handle = torch._C._to_dlpack(tensor)
        self.name = self.get_name()
    def get_name(self):
        ctypes.pythonapi.PyCapsule_GetName.restype = ctypes.c_char_p
        ctypes.pythonapi.PyCapsule_GetName.argtypes = [ctypes.py_object]
        return ctypes.pythonapi.PyCapsule_GetName(self.handle)
    def to_torch(self):
        return torch._C._from_dlpack(self.handle)
    @property
    def _tvm_handle(self):
        ctypes.pythonapi.PyCapsule_GetPointer.restype = ctypes.c_void_p
        ctypes.pythonapi.PyCapsule_GetPointer.argtypes = [ctypes.py_object, ctypes.c_char_p]
        return ctypes.pythonapi.PyCapsule_GetPointer(self.handle, self.name)
```

@notorca Thanks for the clarification! I see, so the problem is related to hardware. I tried to reduce the number of threads (num_thread_x) here: https://github.com/dmlc/tvm/blob/master/topi/python/topi/cuda/conv2d_nchw.py#L250
And when it's changed to 8 instead of 64 (https://github.com/dmlc/tvm/blob/master/topi/python/topi/cuda/conv2d_nchw.py#L255) or 16 (https://github.com/dmlc/tvm/blob/master/topi/python/topi/cuda/conv2d_nchw.py#L298), W.shared becomes [float32 * 584]. 
@tqchen Maybe we should use parameters specific to hardware just like "tvm.target.current_target(allow_none=False).max_num_threads"?

I agree to enable it by default.
@ma-xiaodong  To support more pragma, for now you can register tvm_callback_opencl_postproc.

```python
@tvm.register_func
def tvm_callback_opencl_postproc(code):
    code = "#pragma  xxx" + code
    return code
```
